cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and the analysis of stylistic patterns in written texts using complex network concepts and methods from dynamical systems theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also employs statistical methods and intermittency measurements, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of complex network topology analysis suggests a possible fit with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), while the application of these methods to authorship recognition indicates a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
